article.headline: UC Santa Barbara 83, Cal Poly 81
article.story: SANTA BARBARA, Calif. -- Kyle Boswell's three-point play with 12 seconds left in the second overtime gave UC Santa Barbara an 83-81 victory over Cal Poly on Saturday. Boswell, who finished with 23 points, also made three free throws after being fouled trying a 3-pointer with 1:06 left in the second OT period, giving the Gauchos (7-10, 3-3 Big West) an 80-79 lead. Drake U'u scored for Cal Poly with 29 seconds left to put the Mustangs in front by a point. Taran Brown had 15 points for UCSB, including a 3-pointer in the final minute of regulation to tie the game at 66. Nate Garth had 13 points and eight assists, and Michael Bryson and Mitch Brewe scored 10 points apiece. Reese Morgan led the Mustangs (7-9, 3-3) with 26 points, including seven 3-pointers. Chris Eversley had 16 points and 15 rebounds for Cal Poly, which hasn't won at Santa Barbara since 2007.
